    "Finally, from z ′′ ∈ S ′ and z ′′ ⊑ z ′ ⊑ z ⊑ x, we have z ′′ ⊑ ′ x.",
    "Hence we have a z ′′ ⊑ ′ x such that z ′′ ∈ X ′ and z ′′ ̸ ∈ Y ′, so x ̸ ∈ X ′ ⊃ ′ Y ′.For (c), the right-to-left inclusion is again straightforward.",
    "For the leftto-right inclusion, suppose x ∈ S ′ but x ̸ ∈ ■ i X, so there is a y such that xR i y and y ̸ ∈ X.",
    "Then by refinability for X, there is a u ⊑ y such that for all u ′ ⊑ u, u ′ ̸ ∈ X.",
    "By Definition 5.52.5, since x ∈ S ′, xR i y, and u ⊑ y, there is a z ∈ S ′ such that z ≬ u andxR i z, so xR ′ i z."
